# Real-world Data Project

## Objective
Analyze and predict business performance using a real-world retail sales dataset.

## Domain
Retail Sales Analysis

## Libraries Used
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Scikit-learn

## Features
- Data cleaning and preprocessing
- Statistical analysis
- Correlation analysis
- Data visualization
- Sales and profit analysis
- Machine learning prediction
- Insight generation

## Machine Learning Algorithm
- Linear Regression

## Visualizations
- Top 10 Products by Sales
- Sales by Region
- Correlation Heatmap
- Actual vs Predicted Profit Graph

## Model Evaluation
- Mean Squared Error (MSE)
- R2 Score

## Insights
- Certain products generate significantly higher sales.
- Sales performance varies across regions.
- Sales and profit are positively correlated.
- High discounts can reduce overall profit.

## Outcome
Applied data science concepts on a real-world retail dataset including data cleaning, exploratory data analysis, visualization, and predictive modeling.